# tracking-doc-checkbox-sync-regression-guard — History

## v2.1.0 (2026-06-20)

**Changed by:** ProjectProteus issue #186, a RE-PLANNING session. The first plan
got a NOGO; this entry captures the durable regression-guard learnings of the
re-plan. This is a planning session — the offline-fixture test was NOT implemented
or CI-run.
**Verification:** unverified for the v2.1.0 additions (a design from a re-planning
session; the offline-fixture test shape is unverified until the PR lands and CI runs).
The v2.0.0 core workflow remains `verified-local`; the skill frontmatter `verification`
field is intentionally NOT raised, and the new content is labelled unverified inline.

### What changed (MINOR — additive sub-pattern, no core-workflow change)

- **Policy reconciliation as the REASON to go offline.** Added the explicit anti-pattern:
  a live-`gh`-in-CI test that SKIPs (exit 0) when `gh` is unauthenticated is a FALSE-GREEN
  no-op AND a violation of the repo's anti-silent-failure policy — the `forbid-suppressions`
  job at `.github/workflows/_required.yml:53-105` plus `docs/runbooks/no-silent-failures.md`.
  The reviewer NOGO'd it on P1/KISS + P7/POLA.
- **Mirror-the-PROPERTY rule.** Added the precedent of the repo's existing HERMETIC test
  `tests/dispatch-apply.test.sh` (shims `curl`, fake token, no network) as the model to
  mirror — mirror the hermetic/deterministic PROPERTY, not just the `tests/` file location.
- **Ground-truth at AUTHORING time.** Reaffirmed building the `EXPECTED` map via
  `gh issue view` while planning (not at test time); for #186 this enumerated 38 issues and
  surfaced TWO stale entries (#92, #100) the issue body never mentioned.
- **`# RE-VERIFY:` comment + same-PR rule** to bound snapshot staleness (e.g. a reopened issue):
  fixture and doc change land in the SAME PR.
- **PR-group-scoped ticking rule:** tick a Wave-3 / group box only when EVERY issue on the
  line is CLOSED (groups with open children #98/#101/#103 stay unticked).
- **Runnable "guard-is-not-a-no-op" temp-tree proof:** copy the test into `$work/tests/` so its
  `$0`-relative `REPO_ROOT` retargets the temp tree, introduce drift, run it, assert nonzero exit.
- **Six new Failed Attempts rows** (all tagged #186): live-`gh` skip-on-unauth required test;
  claimed-to-mirror-but-inverted-the-property; 41 network calls for a static fact; trusted the
  issue body's stale-entry list (omitted #92/#100); treated PR-group lines as per-issue;
  verification step that says "point the test at `$tmp`" without doing it.
- Bumped version 2.0.0 -> 2.1.0; date 2026-06-20.

### Why

The v2.0.0 entry established the offline committed-fixture design as the answer to the
live-`gh` NOGO. The #186 re-plan independently rediscovered the SAME core lesson and added
the missing connective tissue: WHY offline is mandatory (the repo's `forbid-suppressions` /
`no-silent-failures` policy, not just determinism), WHAT to mirror (the hermetic property of
`dispatch-apply.test.sh`), and HOW to PROVE the guard is not a no-op (an actually-executed
temp-tree drift proof, after a reviewer flagged an unexecuted hand-wave). These are additive,
so MINOR — the core EXPECT-table workflow is unchanged.

